        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"thrush\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"72103\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/45deac/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> thrush:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I didn’t realize Signal was displaying via Chromium. It’s certainly plausible that something changed with how Chromium rendering is handled that would explain the identical behavior in both Signal and Vivaldi. I’ll try falling back to X11.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yeah, these default to X11 still, unfortunately, so you would be running them in X11, over XWayland, in an experimental Wayland session. Definitely not ideal.</p>\n<p>Given you’re using the official package of course</p>",
